<title>USA: RESEARCH ALERT - Synopsys Inc.</title>
<headline>RESEARCH ALERT - Synopsys Inc.</headline>
<dateline>LOS ANGELES 1997-07-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>Hambrecht and Quist analyst Doug van Dorsten said he downgraded Synopsys Inc to a hold from a buy, citing a belief the company's share valuation &quot;is a bit full at current levels, and that upside in the share price is limited for the next couple of quarters.&quot;</p>
<p>--He also trimmed earnings estimates for fiscal 1997 to $1.52 per share from $1.56, and for fiscal 1998 to $1.92 from $2.00.</p>
<p>--&quot;Management indicated sale and EPS growth is expected to be 20 percent to 25 percent in future quarters, down from a prior target of 25 percent to 30 percent. The lower reported growth is meant to help build backlog at a more rapid pace, and smooth out revenue during a given quarter.&quot;</p>
</text>
